Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Place Order (UC3), Validate Payment (UC5), Place Order --include--> Validate Payment
   Explanation: "Validate Payment" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Place Order", UC3). It is not associated with any actor directly. It does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not involved in any generalization. "Validate Payment" represents a decomposed step of placing an order rather than a complete, standalone service observable to an actor. This constitutes the Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship antipattern.
